# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Disintegrate — X damage + exile-on-death (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-499 closed Disintegrate as WORKING but carried NO scripted
# puzzle with semantic assertions (the pre-existing disintegrate_exiles_creature.pzl
# is golden-log-only with no [assertions] section, heuristic-driven). This audit
# puzzle SCRIPTS the cast and asserts the distinctive replacement effect.
#
# Disintegrate is {X}{R} sorcery: "deals X damage to any target. If it's a
# creature, it can't be regenerated this turn, and if it would die this turn,
# exile it instead." (SP$ DealDamage | NumDmg$ X | ReplaceDyingDefined$
# ThisTargetedCard.Creature). The replacement (CR 614) sends a lethally-damaged
# creature to EXILE, not the graveyard.
#
# X is funded by mana: P0 has exactly 4 Mountains, paying {X}{R} at X=3, so
# Disintegrate deals 3 to a 2/2 Grizzly Bears — lethal — and the bears is EXILED
# (not put in the graveyard).
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-499):
#   1. Parses + castable as a {X}{R} sorcery (spell cast assertion).
#   2. X-paid damage: 4 Mountains -> X=3 to the chosen creature.
#   3. ReplaceDyingDefined exile-on-death: the lethally-damaged creature goes to
#      EXILE, and is NOT in the graveyard (the discriminating assertions).
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Disintegrate in hand, 4 Mountains (-> X=3 + {R}).
#   - P1: a Grizzly Bears (2/2) it controls.
#   - Script: P0 casts Disintegrate at the Grizzly Bears; 3 damage is lethal;
#     the bears is exiled, not put in P1's graveyard.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Disintegrate Exiles a Lethally-Damaged Creature
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Disintegrate ({X}{R} sorcery) at P1's 2/2 Grizzly Bears with X=3 (4 Mountains). The 3 damage is lethal, and the ReplaceDyingDefined clause EXILES the creature instead of putting it in the graveyard. Backs issue mtg-499 (DealDamageXPaid + exile-on-death replacement; CR 614).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Disintegrate
p0battlefield=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain
p0library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears
p1library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

[p0_script]
# Cast Disintegrate at P1's Grizzly Bears. With 4 Mountains the engine pays
# {X}{R} at X=3, dealing 3 (lethal to the 2/2).
cast Disintegrate targeting Grizzly Bears

[assertions]
# The X-burn sorcery was actually cast.
spell cast Disintegrate
# The lethally-damaged creature was EXILED (replacement effect), so it is in
# P1's exile zone...
opponent exile contains Grizzly Bears
# ...and it is NOT in P1's graveyard (this is what distinguishes Disintegrate
# from ordinary lethal burn — the exile replacement, CR 614).
NOT opponent graveyard contains Grizzly Bears
